Charge: 25/25</font></font></p></p>
<hr>
<i>Posted by Sullla on Sep 15, 2002 03:03 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>No offense to Thunderfall, but what he typed really wasn't the point of the screenshot at all. <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt=""> The point is that in a Deity game you have to lie low in the early game, allow the other civs to walk all over your territory, let them fight massive battles near your cities, and so on in the hopes that you can catch them later after they waste hundreds of shields fighting pointless wars. Having a strong military is important, but I was really trying to demonstrate the importance of letting the AI walk all over you when you are not strong enough to fight back against them. THAT's the lesson you should take from this; don't do something stupid and refuse an AI demand when they have this kind of force to punish you with. You can always have your revenge later, as I did in this game. <img src="images/smilies/cool.gif" border="0" alt=""><p><font face="Verdana, Arial" size="2">__________________<br>
Former GOTM Player, now competing in the <a href="http://realmsbeyond.net/civ/epics.html" target="_blank">Realms Beyond Civilization Epics</a>.<br />
<a href="http://www.kalikokottage.com/civ3/sullla/" target="_blank">Sullla's Civ3 page</a>: 17 tournament games, 4 solo games, a PBEM game, 6 strategy pages, and much more.   <br />
<br />
"Iacta alea est."         - G. Julius Caesar</font></p></p>
