<i>Posted by foodguy on Sep 16, 2002 06:37 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>I recently finished a game just like that -- though certainly not on deity. i was playing normal map, 7 civs. 5 of them wound up on this moderate-sized island and 4 of them (me excluded) were constantly at war with later-game MPs with the other two civs. and my nation controlled the wide isthmus that separated them all. weird. at first i tried chasing them off my property, but it just got to the point that i would have been constantly at war, too. so i let them go at each other and tried trading resources/techs to the losers to keep them in the game. i won a diplomatic victory in like 1814 or something. i was the only one they could agree they didn't hate.</p>
